WHO   — Nadsat — the teen tongue · the reader's conditioning
WHAT  — The book's form-as-theme: the reader learns the language by immersion, conditioned painlessly while reading about conditioning.
WHERE — ACO · A CLOCKWORK ORANGE  Framework inputs: A Clockwork Orange (Anthony Burgess, 1962)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the warning is enacted on you — you are gently programmed in a new tongue, never noticing it happen.
HOW   — By repetition and context, until ‘ultra-violence’ in an alien argot becomes intimate and even beautiful.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the slang you learned without a dictionary — proof, in your own pleasured reading, of how easily and invisibly a mind can be conditioned.

